 **Relational Channel** (does the interpr", "suggestion": "Define \"Bicameral Review\" on first use: Bicameral Review (two independent review channels that must both approve an output before it reaches the user \u2014 neither can override the other)"}, {"requirement": "BMT-1", "line_number": 148, "excerpt": "Governance is a compiler, not a document. The constitution defines a type system for power. A type s", "suggestion": "Define \"TLC\" on first use: TLC (The Living Constitution \u2014 the runtime enforcement system built alongside this research that applies constitutional rules to AI behavior session by session)"}, {"requirement": "BMT-1", "line_number": 152, "excerpt": "The Contract Window is not theoretical. It is implemented in Python and operational at https://githu", "suggestion": "Define \"Contract Window\" on first use: Contract Window (a structured record of what a human-AI session is trying to accomplish, what has been verified, and who is responsible for fixing errors)"}, {"requirement": "BMT-1", "line_number": 158, "excerpt": "The theoretical framework did not precede the evidence. It emerged from it. Over months of extended ", "suggestion": "Define \"tlc\" on first use: TLC (The Living Constitution \u2014 the runtime enforcement system built alongside this research that applies constitutional rules to AI behavior session by session)"}, {"requirement": "BMT-1", "line_number": 160, "excerpt": "**Observation 1 \u2014 V&T as cognitive anchor.** [Evidence type: A, E] Sessions conducted from February ", "suggestion": "Define \"V&T\" on first use: V&T (Verification and Truth \u2014 a statement that explicitly separates what is confirmed from what is proposed, and states the functional status of the work)"}, {"requirement": "BMT-1", "line_number": 160, "excerpt": "**Observation 1 \u2014 V&T as cognitive anchor.** [Evidence type: A, E] Sessions conducted from February ", "suggestion": "Define \"tlc\" on first use: TLC (The Living Constitution \u2014 the runtim